[Following the recent PRRS outbreaks, the Vietnamese Ministry of
Agriculture has issued regulations on the control and prevention of PRRS.
The regulations focus on the control and prevention of PRRS, stressing on
the supervision and early discovery of the epidemic, and a tightened
control of slaughtering and transportation of pigs and pork products. They
are applicable to all State agencies, Vietnamese and foreign individuals
and organisations, specialising in the raising, slaughtering and
transportation of pigs on the Vietnamese territories. (Source
<http://www.pigprogress.net/news/id1602-60248/vietnamese_ministry_issues_prrs_regulations.html>).

On 23 Feb 2008, Viet Nam submitted to the OIE its 4th and final report on
PRRS, including a map showing the country-wide disseminated outbreaks; see
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=6831>
and posting 20080507.1562. According to the report, "the event is unlikely
to be contained and is now considered to be endemic. No more follow-up
reports will be made, but instead, information about this disease will be
included in the future six-monthly reports." - Mod.AS]
